    "export_view": {
      "value": "<p>The Ticket Items section of a ticket lists all services/items added to the ticket in line-item fashion. There are various actions and categories used to view details, update quantities, add a discount, mark items as defective, and more. These fields help you fine-tune the data collected when a ticket is closed, ensuring your inventory, metrics, and reporting remain accurate.</p><p><strong>Note</strong>: Access to certain fields may be restricted by the Role assigned to the user.</p><h2 id=\"EditingTicketItems-AdditionalResources\">Additional Resources</h2><ul><li><p><a href=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/spaces/SCD/pages/1930494512/Creating+a+Quick+Sale+Ticket\" data-linked-resource-id=\"1930494512\" data-linked-resource-version=\"14\" data-linked-resource-type=\"page\">Creating a Quick Sale Ticket</a></p></li><li><p><a href=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/spaces/SCD/pages/1933803723/Create+a+Repair+Ticket\" data-linked-resource-id=\"1933803723\" data-linked-resource-version=\"13\" data-linked-resource-type=\"page\">Creating a Repair Ticket</a></p></li><li><p><a href=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/spaces/SCD/pages/1928921152/Staff+Management+Roles+and+Permissions\" data-linked-resource-id=\"1928921152\" data-linked-resource-version=\"18\" data-linked-resource-type=\"page\">Roles and Permissions</a></p></li><li><p><a href=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/spaces/SCD/pages/2098036767/Discount+Management+on+Tickets\" data-linked-resource-id=\"2098036767\" data-linked-resource-version=\"5\" data-linked-resource-type=\"page\">Discount Management on Tickets</a></p></li><li><p><a href=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/spaces/SCD/pages/1932361958/Print+Settings+-+Receipt+Template\" data-linked-resource-id=\"1932361958\" data-linked-resource-version=\"7\" data-linked-resource-type=\"page\">Print Settings - Receipts</a></p></li><li><p><a href=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/spaces/SCD/pages/1932853380/Assigning+Ticket+Items+to+Users\" data-linked-resource-id=\"1932853380\" data-linked-resource-version=\"4\" data-linked-resource-type=\"page\">Assigning Ticket Items to Users</a></p></li><li><p><a href=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/spaces/SCD/pages/1932525631/Return+Merchandise+Authorization+RMA+Tracking+Resources\" data-linked-resource-id=\"1932525631\" data-linked-resource-version=\"6\" data-linked-resource-type=\"page\">Return Merchandise Authorization (RMA) Tracking Resources</a></p></li><li><p><a href=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/spaces/SCD/pages/1932787785/Catalog+Items+Bundle+Setup\" data-linked-resource-id=\"1932787785\" data-linked-resource-version=\"21\" data-linked-resource-type=\"page\">Catalog Items: Bundle Setup</a></p></li><li><p><a href=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/spaces/SCD/pages/1933541561/Sales+Tax+Override\" data-linked-resource-id=\"1933541561\" data-linked-resource-version=\"6\" data-linked-resource-type=\"page\">Sales Tax Override</a></p></li><li><p><a href=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/spaces/SCD/pages/1932624055/Inventory+Status+Overview\" data-linked-resource-id=\"1932624055\" data-linked-resource-version=\"7\" data-linked-resource-type=\"page\">Inventory Status: What Does It Mean?</a></p></li></ul><span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper image-center-wrapper confluence-embedded-manual-size\"><img class=\"confluence-embedded-image image-center\" alt=\"Technical - 124a6d.png\" width=\"760\" src=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/1933705370/Technical%20-%20124a6d.png?api=v2\"></span><h2 id=\"EditingTicketItems-EditingaTicket\">Editing a Ticket</h2><p>In Ticket View mode, you can begin editing the ticket by clicking the <strong>Edit button (pencil icon)</strong> near the top-right of the page.</p><span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper image-center-wrapper confluence-embedded-manual-size\"><img class=\"confluence-embedded-image image-center\" alt=\"Edit Ticket Item 1.png\" width=\"757\" src=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/1933705370/Edit%20Ticket%20Item%201.png?api=v2\"></span><h2 id=\"EditingTicketItems-EditingTicketItems\">Editing Ticket Items</h2><p>In Ticket-edit mode, the <strong>Ticket Items</strong> section lists all items added to the ticket in line-item fashion. Below, we\u2019ve listed the various actions you can take when modifying a Ticket Item.</p><span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper image-center-wrapper confluence-embedded-manual-size\"><img class=\"confluence-embedded-image image-center\" alt=\"Edit Ticket Item 2.png\" width=\"760\" src=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/1933705370/Edit%20Ticket%20Item%202.png?api=v2\"></span><h3 id=\"EditingTicketItems-DiscountAllTicketItems\">Discount All Ticket Items</h3><span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper image-center-wrapper confluence-embedded-manual-size\"><img class=\"confluence-embedded-image image-center\" alt=\"Edit Ticket Item 3.png\" width=\"760\" src=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/1933705370/Edit%20Ticket%20Item%203.png?api=v2\"></span><p>This will discount every\u00a0item in the ticket, either by a percentage or a dollar amount. The discount is divided evenly among ticket items (for example, a 10% ticket discount will apply a 10% discount to each valid ticket item).</p><h3 id=\"EditingTicketItems-SerialNumberEntry\">Serial Number Entry</h3><span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper image-center-wrapper confluence-embedded-manual-size\"><img class=\"confluence-embedded-image image-center\" alt=\"Edit Ticket Item 4.png\" width=\"760\" src=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/1933705370/Edit%20Ticket%20Item%204.png?api=v2\"></span><p>When adding a serialized item to a ticket, you are required to enter the Serial Number for the device/item that you are selling to pull it from inventory to add it to the list. You will not be able to save/progress the ticket until the corresponding item is pulled or removed from the list.</p><h3 id=\"EditingTicketItems-CatalogItemDetails\">Catalog Item Details</h3><span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper image-center-wrapper confluence-embedded-manual-size\"><img class=\"confluence-embedded-image image-center\" alt=\"Edit Ticket Item 5.png\" width=\"760\" src=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/1933705370/Edit%20Ticket%20Item%205.png?api=v2\"></span><p>Click on the magnifying glass icon next to the Catalog Item field to see some general information about the item. There is also a link to view the full inventory details for that catalog item (this will open in a new tab).</p><span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper image-center-wrapper confluence-embedded-manual-size\"><img class=\"confluence-embedded-image image-center\" alt=\"Edit Ticket Item 6.png\" width=\"359\" src=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/1933705370/Edit%20Ticket%20Item%206.png?api=v2\"></span><h3 id=\"EditingTicketItems-TicketItemNotes\">Ticket Item Notes</h3><span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper image-center-wrapper confluence-embedded-manual-size\"><img class=\"confluence-embedded-image image-center\" alt=\"Edit Ticket Item 7.png\" width=\"760\" src=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/1933705370/Edit%20Ticket%20Item%207.png?api=v2\"></span><p>Add a note to a ticket item for additional reminders and details. This can be useful when using placeholder items for special orders, etc.</p><p><strong>Note</strong>: Ticket Item notes can be visible on receipts based on your receipt template settings.</p><h3 id=\"EditingTicketItems-TicketItemRelations\">Ticket Item Relations</h3><span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper image-center-wrapper confluence-embedded-manual-size\"><img class=\"confluence-embedded-image image-center\" alt=\"Edit Ticket Item 8.png\" width=\"760\" src=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/1933705370/Edit%20Ticket%20Item%208.png?api=v2\"></span><p>The Relations column is used to link a staff member with a sale of an item and/or the repair service they performed. If there are multiple repair devices on a Repair Ticket, you can also link the service/part to the correct device. Relations are used in various reports to track sales, productivity, return repairs, and other metrics.</p><h3 id=\"EditingTicketItems-Quantity/Hours\">Quantity/Hours</h3><span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper image-center-wrapper confluence-embedded-manual-size\"><img class=\"confluence-embedded-image image-center\" alt=\"Edit Ticket Item 9.png\" width=\"760\" src=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/1933705370/Edit%20Ticket%20Item%209.png?api=v2\"></span><p>This field is used to view the quantity of an item added to a ticket and/or applying labor hours to a service. Depending on your Item Type settings, labor can be tracked at a fixed rate (the price does not change, regardless of hours entered) or a variable rate (the price increases as more hours are entered). Labor Hours are recorded alongside the associated staff member\u2019s hourly rate. This is used for Wage Expenses and other reporting.</p><h3 id=\"EditingTicketItems-Line-ItemDiscount\">Line-Item Discount</h3><span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper image-center-wrapper confluence-embedded-manual-size\"><img class=\"confluence-embedded-image image-center\" alt=\"Edit Ticket Item 10.png\" width=\"760\" src=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/1933705370/Edit%20Ticket%20Item%2010.png?api=v2\"></span><p>This field allows you to discount a single item, by either a percentage or dollar amount. Click the Edit button to begin entering the discount.</p><h2 id=\"EditingTicketItems-TicketItemActions\">Ticket Item Actions</h2><p>These actions are in the final column of the line item </p><p>Note: Actions will vary based on the Item Type of the item, Ticket Settings, and the Role assigned to the user accessing the ticket.</p><span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper image-center-wrapper confluence-embedded-manual-size\"><img class=\"confluence-embedded-image image-center\" alt=\"Edit Ticket Item 11.png\" width=\"760\" src=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/1933705370/Edit%20Ticket%20Item%2011.png?api=v2\"></span><h3 id=\"EditingTicketItems-MarkanItemasDamaged/Defective\">Mark an Item as Damaged/Defective</h3><span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper image-center-wrapper confluence-embedded-manual-size\"><img class=\"confluence-embedded-image image-center\" alt=\"Edit Ticket Item 12.png\" width=\"155\" src=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/1933705370/Edit%20Ticket%20Item%2012.png?api=v2\"></span><p>To flag an item as Damaged or Defective, click the thumbs-down icon. This will open a pop-up with a form to add notes, and, choose an inventory status, and, depending on your settings, choose a reason for marking the item as such.</p><p><strong>Note</strong>: Marking an item as defective will initiate the RMA Process. If you accidentally flag the item as defective, an Admin can edit the item back to Instock status when viewing the Item Details.</p><h3 id=\"EditingTicketItems-Bundle/AttachaItem\">Bundle/Attach a Item</h3><span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper image-center-wrapper confluence-embedded-manual-size\"><img class=\"confluence-embedded-image image-center\" alt=\"Edit Ticket Item 16.png\" width=\"149\" src=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/1933705370/Edit%20Ticket%20Item%2016.png?api=v2\"></span><p>When a service or part is added that can be bundled as a Parent Item, click the Bundle icon (chain link) to search for parts/items that will be added as a Child Item. The Child Item will be noted as such under the Parent Item.</p><span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper image-center-wrapper confluence-embedded-manual-size\"><img class=\"confluence-embedded-image image-center\" alt=\"Edit Ticket Item 19.png\" width=\"760\" src=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/1933705370/Edit%20Ticket%20Item%2019.png?api=v2\"></span><h3 id=\"EditingTicketItems-WaiveCharge\">Waive Charge</h3><span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper image-center-wrapper confluence-embedded-manual-size\"><img class=\"confluence-embedded-image image-center\" alt=\"Edit Ticket Item 17.png\" width=\"149\" src=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/1933705370/Edit%20Ticket%20Item%2017.png?api=v2\"></span><p>Click the Currency icon to waive the charge/fee for the line item. This is often used for Return Repair (Rework) Tickets. Items with waived charges will be marked accordingly on the line item. Any waived charges can be viewed on the Waived Charge Report.</p><p><strong>Note</strong>: To undo the waived charge, click the icon again.</p><span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper image-center-wrapper confluence-embedded-manual-size\"><img class=\"confluence-embedded-image image-center\" alt=\"Edit Ticket Item 20.png\" width=\"760\" src=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/1933705370/Edit%20Ticket%20Item%2020.png?api=v2\"></span><h3 id=\"EditingTicketItems-ItemOverrides-SupplierOverride/TaxOverride\">Item Overrides - Supplier Override/Tax Override</h3><span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper image-center-wrapper confluence-embedded-manual-size\"><img class=\"confluence-embedded-image image-center\" alt=\"Edit Ticket Item 13.png\" width=\"155\" src=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/1933705370/Edit%20Ticket%20Item%2013.png?api=v2\"></span><p>Click the Asterisk to override details for the line item. You can override the Supplier for the inventory item and (based on your Ticket Settings) taxable amount for the item.</p><p><strong>Note</strong>: The taxable amount field is the dollar amount that taxes will be applied toward.</p><span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper image-center-wrapper confluence-embedded-manual-size\"><img class=\"confluence-embedded-image image-center\" alt=\"Edit Ticket Item 22.png\" width=\"323\" src=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/1933705370/Edit%20Ticket%20Item%2022.png?api=v2\"></span><h3 id=\"EditingTicketItems-RemoveanItem\">Remove an Item</h3><span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper image-center-wrapper confluence-embedded-manual-size\"><img class=\"confluence-embedded-image image-center\" alt=\"Edit Ticket Item 14.png\" width=\"155\" src=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/1933705370/Edit%20Ticket%20Item%2014.png?api=v2\"></span><p>To remove an item from a ticket click the X icon. If you are removing an inventoried item, a pop-up will appear, so you can select the appropriate inventory status to place the item.</p><span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper image-center-wrapper confluence-embedded-manual-size\"><img class=\"confluence-embedded-image image-center\" alt=\"Edit Ticket Item 21.png\" width=\"272\" src=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/1933705370/Edit%20Ticket%20Item%2021.png?api=v2\"></span><p /><p /><p>START 1.20.X</p>",
